<section xml:id="history-of-computers_the-first-generation">
  <title>The First Generation</title>
  <p>Generations of computers are largely defined by the components used to build them. Although mechanical computers
    like Babbage’s Engines and the Hollerith desk would continue to see use well into the 20th century,
    mathematicians and engineers in the 1930s realized that the logic of computation - Boolean logic - could be
    implemented with electronic relays and switches. <term>Vacuum tubes</term>, an electrical component that can be used
    as a switching device, became the core components of the first electrical computers.</p>
